metadata.description:
Sea anemones are a group of predatory marine animals of the order Actiniaria (from Wikipedia).

The number of Traits in this collection is 10 (134 layers) and it has the ability to make 31,500,000,000 different Monkeys.

Some â€‹layers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.

metadata.name: System Î² #307
metadata.description:
Î± -> Î² is about "Increases in magnitude and decreases in computation". And still related the fleeting time in the generating process.

My role in this work is more of a discoverer than a creator. 

Try to reveal the possibilities of time perception in the generative art through negotiating with incomprehensible mathematical equations.

What I want to explore through this work is that behind the generated results, the dynamic process of generations are equally diverse and unpredictable.

When we watch the generating process displayed on the computer, changing instantly, moving, multiplying, disappearing, and we hesitate, wonder, pause, await, as if many possibilities of time perception have emerged in the fragmented moments.

metadata.name: Unfinished Loom #376
metadata.description:
The 'Unfinished Loom' is a generative system that produces variations of itself through rotations, displacements, and self-repetition. 

Self-similarity in the loom is achieved by repeating the double grid system and its elements vertically (using the 'o' and 'l' keys) and horizontally (using the 'i' and 'k' keys).

Pressing 'a' produces automatic changes, while pressing 'x' reverts to the original composition.

By clicking on the canvas, you can play with colors and transparency. 

The '1' key toggles between disorder and order. 
The '2' and '3' keys allow you to toggle displacements.
The '4' key enables you to switch between entropy or not.
The '5' key lets you switch between mixed textures or assigned textures. 

You can reduce, amplify, or flip the displacement using the 'u' or 'j' key. 
To remove a color press 'c'. To reset to all colors, press 'v'.

You can save a PNG file using 's', a JPG using 'd', a PNG with twice your window height using 'f', and a print size image using 'g'.

This work explores composition based on generative double grid system, where rotations, displacements and noisy lines intertwine to form a playful loom.

Created with p5.js rendering in WEBGL.

metadata.name: Esplorazione #2
metadata.description:
Exploration can be seen as a fundamental aspect of human nature, as it drives us to seek out new knowledge, experiences, and understanding of the world around us. It is a never-ending quest for truth, for understanding the unknown and the mysterious.

Philosophically, exploration can be seen as a means of self-discovery and self-actualization. By venturing into the unknown, we are forced to confront our own limitations, biases and assumptions. We are also presented with new perspectives and ways of understanding, which can challenge and broaden our own understanding of the world and ourselves.

Exploration can be seen as a form of self-expression and artistic creativity. It allows us to test the boundaries of what is possible, to push the limits of what we know, and to discover new and innovative ways of seeing the world.

It can be understood as a fundamental aspect of human existence, one that allows us to transcend our individual selves and to connect with the greater world around us. It is a never-ending quest for truth, for understanding the unknown and the mysterious, and for discovering our own place in the world.

Press [s] to download the canvas in original resolution.

created via p5.js // CC-BY-SA // twt: @twirizzo

metadata.name: Reversed #20
metadata.description:
This collection captures the spirit of the mountains, where the ridge blends into sky and earth. The inversion of the image evokes the philosophy that sometimes, to better understand nature and art, you have to look at things from a different angle, to reveal a new perspective, a new balance.

##Features
Palette, Moon, Stars, BlendMode, Negative Mode.

Made with p5js

metadata.name: All The Way #110
metadata.description:
"All the Way" is a visually stunning and dynamic generative art piece that is sure to make a striking addition to any art collection. Created using the programming language p5js, this artwork is truly one of a kind and cannot be replicated.

The vibrant colors, fluid shapes, and dynamic movement in "All the Way" make it an ideal centerpiece for any space. The constantly shifting shapes and colors create a sense of energy and motion that will draw the eye and captivate the viewer. This piece is perfect for anyone who loves abstract art or is looking for something unique and eye-catching to add to their collection.

Additionally, the theme of "All the Way" is one that is sure to resonate with many people. The artwork represents the flow of life, the power of creativity, and the endless possibilities that exist in the world around us. This makes it an ideal choice for anyone who values personal growth, exploration, and a sense of adventure.

Whether you're an art collector, an art enthusiast, or simply someone who appreciates beautiful and thought-provoking art, "All the Way" is a must-have addition to your collection. With its dynamic and abstract style, this piece is sure to spark conversations and inspire new ideas. Don't miss out on the chance to own a truly unique and captivating artwork that you will enjoy for years to come!

To save image press "s"
To save image in high quality add &print=2 or &print=3 in the live URL then press "s".

Note: Image can take a minute to render.

Created using p5js and p5js pattern
Created By Winston
Feb 2023
